WEBVTT

00:04.170 --> 00:05.990
CONNOR:
It's a terrible thing

00:06.040 --> 00:09.430
when someone loses
theIr moral compass.

00:09.480 --> 00:10.788
It starts with
a small infraction,

00:10.830 --> 00:12.218
something insignificant.

00:12.270 --> 00:13.965
Then it's followecl
by two more Infractions

00:14.010 --> 00:17.138
because the first one has
long been expected as Justified.

00:17.190 --> 00:20.409
Then, like a pyramid scheme
of moral laxity,

00:20.450 --> 00:23.271
the lies become misdemeanors,

00:23.320 --> 00:24.571
the misdemeanors
become felonies,

00:24.630 --> 00:26.143
and the felonies
become a way of life.

00:26.200 --> 00:29.454
And that brings us
to the defendant,

00:29.500 --> 00:31.764
Governor Peter Florrick.

00:31.810 --> 00:33.846
It also brings us
to his enablers,

00:33.900 --> 00:36.289
his campaign manager, Eli Gold,

00:36.340 --> 00:38.467
and-- I'm sorry to say--

00:38.510 --> 00:42.332
his wife, Alicia Florrick.

00:42.390 --> 00:45.029
Now, Mrs. Florrick will be
sitting behind her husband

00:45.080 --> 00:47.423
every day in court.

00:47.480 --> 00:49.823
In this way, the defense
wants you to think warmly

00:49.870 --> 00:51.121
of Governor Florrick.

00:51.180 --> 00:52.659
Huh, if his wife
stands beside him,

00:52.700 --> 00:54.008
he can't be that bad.

00:54.050 --> 00:56.359
Well, I want you
to resist that temptation,

00:56.400 --> 00:58.129
and I will give you
a good reason.

00:58.180 --> 01:00.262
Alicia Florrick is part
of a criminal conspiracy...

01:00.320 --> 01:01.309
DIANE:
Objection, Your Honor,

01:01.360 --> 01:02.918
Mrs. Florrick is not on trial.

01:02.970 --> 01:04.483
CONNOR:
I didn't say she was on trial,

01:04.540 --> 01:06.144
I said you were cynically
using her presence...

01:06.190 --> 01:07.361
DIANE:
Excuse me, you Just accused

01:07.410 --> 01:08.798
her of criminal conspiracy.

01:08.850 --> 01:10.238
If anyone is being cynical...

01:10.280 --> 01:12.362
Excuse me, Your Honor,
this is my opening argument

01:12.420 --> 01:13.933
and the defense attorney
will have her chance...

01:13.980 --> 01:17.199
What is cynical, sir,
is to point to a wife

01:17.250 --> 01:18.854
who has stood by
her husband for years.

01:18.900 --> 01:20.629
And if she were not here,

01:20.680 --> 01:22.284
you would point to
thatas suspicious.Your Honor...

01:22.340 --> 01:24.683
No, I'm gonna let you two
burn yourselves out, okay?

01:24.730 --> 01:27.381
Is there anything else?
Are you done, Ms. Lockhart?

01:27.430 --> 01:29.204
I am, Your Honor. As you know,
I came late to this case.

01:29.260 --> 01:31.421
As you pointedly
keep reminding us

01:31.480 --> 01:34.210
over and over and over.
Do you see this?

01:34.260 --> 01:35.386
Yes.
And do you see

01:35.440 --> 01:37.567
the hash mark
that you have there?

01:37.610 --> 01:39.043
Yes.
Okay, every time

01:39.090 --> 01:41.263
one of you provokes
a round of crosstalk,

01:41.310 --> 01:43.221
you get a mark,
and whoever has

01:43.270 --> 01:45.875
the most at the end of the day
will be held

01:45.930 --> 01:49.309
in contempt and fined $10,000.
Now, isn't that fun?

01:49.370 --> 01:50.792
Well, it is... unusual.

01:50.840 --> 01:52.182
Okay.

01:52.240 --> 01:53.753
Good. Let's continue.

01:53.800 --> 01:56.360
[whispering]:
He hates me.

01:56.420 --> 01:58.320
He has for years.
I know.

01:58.370 --> 02:01.021
This is not gonna be
a cakewalk.

02:01.070 --> 02:03.152
GARBER: I got a call
around 2:00 am.

02:03.210 --> 02:05.201
that my son had been
involved in a shooting.

02:05.250 --> 02:07.855
I thought at first
he was the one who'd been shot,

02:07.910 --> 02:09.207
but they said
he was the shooter.

02:09.250 --> 02:10.649
And who was he accused
ofshooﬁng?

02:10.690 --> 02:12.169
His girlfriend,
Patty Tanniston.

02:12.210 --> 02:13.905
And what did you do
when you heard about this?

02:13.950 --> 02:15.599
I went to see Peter Florrick.

02:17.130 --> 02:19.086
He was state's attorney
at the time

02:19.130 --> 02:20.916
and my friend.

02:20.960 --> 02:23.565
You are a campaign donor of
Mr. Florrick's, is that right?

02:23.620 --> 02:25.702
GARBER: Yes.CONNOR: Hmm. What did
you ask him?

02:25.750 --> 02:28.571
GARBER:
I told him I didn't want
my son going to jail.

02:28.620 --> 02:30.349
I couldn't imagine
he'd done it, but

02:30.410 --> 02:32.310
the evidence was against him.And what did

02:32.360 --> 02:34.316
Mr. Florrick say?He said, "Lloyd..."

02:34.370 --> 02:37.055
[phone buzzes]"...you know how much
I count on your support.

02:37.110 --> 02:38.930
You have nothing
to worry about."

02:38.980 --> 02:41.062
CONNOR:
And you took this to mean?Exactly what

02:41.110 --> 02:43.578
it sounded like-- he was going
to make the charges go away.

02:43.640 --> 02:45.062
CONNOR:
And what happened after that?

02:45.120 --> 02:47.202
GARBER: Well, two days
into Richie's trial,

02:47.250 --> 02:49.593
some evidence
went missmg.

02:49.640 --> 02:52.905
Bullets that were
in the state crime lab.

02:52.950 --> 02:55.202
The judge declared a mistrial.

02:56.780 --> 02:59.431
What did she say?

02:59.480 --> 03:01.345
Nothing.

03:01.390 --> 03:02.789
She said nothing?

03:02.830 --> 03:04.263
What did you ask?

03:04.310 --> 03:06.358
How's the trial?

03:08.010 --> 03:10.649
Did you piss her off?

03:10.710 --> 03:12.314
What? Is that so unlike you?

03:12.360 --> 03:14.533
She's in Mrs. Florrick mode
for the trial.

03:14.580 --> 03:16.445
That's all.
So you think
he did it?

03:16.500 --> 03:18.798
I don't know.

03:18.850 --> 03:20.977
I think Alicia thinks
he didn't,

03:21.020 --> 03:24.148
but if he goes to prison,
that wouldn't be bad for you.

03:24.200 --> 03:26.191
Lucca.
VVhat?

03:26.240 --> 03:28.151
Can we give it a rest?

03:28.200 --> 03:30.282
Okay.

03:30.340 --> 03:34.208
I'll shut up, but
I speak the truth.

03:40.300 --> 03:42.473
Do you want...?
Do you want...?[thudding continues]

03:42.520 --> 03:44.476
Do you want us to leave?

03:44.520 --> 03:47.045
Not if you don't mind the dust.

03:47.090 --> 03:48.523
[banging]

03:50.960 --> 03:52.393
More expansions?

03:52.440 --> 03:54.260
It looks like it.

03:54.320 --> 03:56.311
I never said that.
Didn't happen.

03:56.360 --> 03:58.009
[phone buzzes]
GOLD:
Connor knows you won't

03:58.060 --> 04:00.312
put Peter on the stand,
so there's no way to rebut.

04:00.370 --> 04:03.407
DIANE: Okay, well, let's see
what I can do, and, uh,

04:03.460 --> 04:04.939
Peter and Alicia,

04:04.980 --> 04:07.062
hold hands, be warm

04:07.110 --> 04:09.715
towards each other.
You're being watched.

04:09.770 --> 04:12.637
The jury wants
to see you close.Doing our best.

04:12.680 --> 04:15.148
CUESTA:
All right, recess is over.

04:15.210 --> 04:17.019
Counselors, do you have
any questions?

04:17.080 --> 04:18.160
Uh, yes, Your Honor.

04:18.210 --> 04:20.940
Mr. Garber, you said you told

04:20.990 --> 04:23.072
Governor Florrick, you couldn't
imagine your son had done it,

04:23.130 --> 04:24.472
but the evidence
was against him.

04:24.520 --> 04:26.340
Is that right?
Yes.

04:26.390 --> 04:28.824
So, this conversation must have
been about the evidence?

04:28.870 --> 04:31.521
I'm sorry?Well, you said the
evidence was against him,

04:31.570 --> 04:35.267
your son, so you must have been
discussing the evidence?

04:35.310 --> 04:36.789
Oh. Right.
Good.

04:36.840 --> 04:38.489
And the governor, your friend,

04:38.530 --> 04:40.998
was familiar with the evidence.

04:41.060 --> 04:42.618
He had just
reviewed it?
Yes.

04:42.670 --> 04:44.183
So then, when
Governor Florrick said,

04:44.240 --> 04:45.969
"You have nothing
to worry about,"

04:46.020 --> 04:47.715
doesn't it make
more sense that

04:47.760 --> 04:49.671
he meant
"I have reviewed the evidence,

04:49.720 --> 04:51.620
and you have nothing
to worry about?"

04:51.680 --> 04:54.285
But that's not what he said.Oh, it's not? Well,

04:54.330 --> 04:56.639
let me read again
exactly what you said.

04:56.680 --> 04:58.329
"I couldn't imagine
he'd done it,

04:58.380 --> 05:00.371
but the evidence
was against him."

05:00.430 --> 05:03.035
And Governor Florrick,
yourfnend,

05:03.080 --> 05:04.775
the friend
you are now betraying...

05:04.820 --> 05:07.380
Objection.Withdrawn. The governor
responded after

05:07.430 --> 05:10.957
reviewing the evidence, "You
have nothing to worry about."

05:11.000 --> 05:13.958
Sir, why can't the governor's
comment, "You have nothing

05:14.000 --> 05:17.128
to worry about"
be interpreted as

05:17.180 --> 05:19.785
the calming commiseration
of a good friend?

05:21.880 --> 05:23.438
Oh, I see you're
looking at Mr. Fox.

05:23.490 --> 05:24.616
Should I ask him?Objection.

05:24.670 --> 05:26.012
CUESTA:
Yeah, sure. Sustained,

05:26.060 --> 05:27.311
but it did look like

05:27.370 --> 05:28.849
he was checking with you
for the answer.

05:28.890 --> 05:31.358
Should I ask again,
Mr. Garber?
No.

05:31.410 --> 05:34.675
It wasn't the commiseration of a
friend, and you know it, Peter.

05:34.720 --> 05:36.676
Excuse me, don't talk
to my client, sir,

05:36.720 --> 05:38.631
especially since you know
he can't talk back.

05:38.680 --> 05:40.466
And enjoy your deal
with the AUSA.

05:40.510 --> 05:42.853
Objection! Your Honor.Yeah, I'm way ahead of you.

05:42.900 --> 05:45.460
Two to one.Wait. No. How did I get one?

05:45.510 --> 05:48.126
Correction. Two to two.

05:48.170 --> 05:50.479
Eight years.

05:50.520 --> 05:52.476
No.

05:52.520 --> 05:55.216
Okay. Then what else do we have
to discuss?

05:55.260 --> 05:58.479
Nothing.

05:58.530 --> 06:00.430
I'll see you in court.Your husband did it,
Mrs. Florrick.

06:00.490 --> 06:02.526
Then prove it.

06:02.570 --> 06:04.356
Seriously.

06:04.400 --> 06:06.186
I've defended enough people

06:06.230 --> 06:08.403
to know how shallow
those words are.

06:08.450 --> 06:10.532
I don't care what you believe.

06:10.580 --> 06:14.277
I care what you can prove,
so prove it.

06:15.810 --> 06:17.971
I have a surprise witness,
Mrs. Florrick.

06:21.200 --> 06:25.113
[phone ringing]

06:25.160 --> 06:27.947
Hey. What's up?ALICIA:
Oh, not much.

06:27.990 --> 06:29.776
I'm being made
into the evil woman here.

06:29.820 --> 06:31.299
Is that Alicia?I need your help.

06:31.340 --> 06:34.639
The AUSA is holding
at eight years.

06:34.690 --> 06:35.998
He says
he has a surprise witness.

06:36.040 --> 06:37.257
Can you find anything out?

06:37.300 --> 06:39.120
Sure. You think it's Cary?Maybe.

06:39.180 --> 06:40.693
I'll talk to Canning.

06:40.740 --> 06:42.742
But anything you can find out
would be helpful.

06:42.790 --> 06:44.303
I'll do my best.

06:44.360 --> 06:45.873
How are youdoing?

06:45.920 --> 06:48.969
Me? I don't know.

06:49.010 --> 06:50.261
I'm exhausted.

06:50.320 --> 06:52.356
[banging]

06:52.410 --> 06:55.629
Where are you? Are you...
are you at a construction site?

06:55.670 --> 06:57.274
The conference room.

06:57.320 --> 06:59.936
The wall is mostly down.

06:59.980 --> 07:02.369
The wall? What wall?

07:02.420 --> 07:03.933
The conference room wall.

07:05.380 --> 07:07.462
DIANE:
Not at Lockhart/Florrick.

07:07.510 --> 07:10.729
It is a pure meritocracy--
where the women decide.[phone beeping]

07:10.770 --> 07:15.298
So come, talk to us, visit
us, let us impress you.

07:17.130 --> 07:18.688
Excuse me. It's my partner.

07:20.910 --> 07:22.514
Hey. Is everything all right?

07:22.570 --> 07:23.912
I don't know.

07:23.960 --> 07:25.825
Are we expanding?

07:25.880 --> 07:27.268
Um, well, yes.

07:27.310 --> 07:28.914
I'm meeting right now
with Shannon Janderman.

07:28.970 --> 07:30.392
I think she's gonna jump ship.

07:30.450 --> 07:32.099
Well, don't you think

07:32.140 --> 07:34.449
it would have been a good idea
to let me know?

07:34.490 --> 07:36.754
Well, what do you mean?
We did discuss this.

07:36.800 --> 07:39.109
I have meetings all week.
I can't cancel them

07:39.150 --> 07:40.458
because of the trial.

07:40.500 --> 07:41.751
No, no, no, the construction.

07:41.800 --> 07:43.586
What construction?

07:43.630 --> 07:45.063
[elevator bell dings]

07:45.110 --> 07:50.116
Oh, my God!

07:50.160 --> 07:53.027
Oh!

07:53.080 --> 07:55.469
How could the...?

07:56.820 --> 07:57.946
Where is David?

07:57.990 --> 07:59.946
How could he let this happen?

08:00.000 --> 08:02.127
Pestilential nuisances
who write for autographs

08:02.170 --> 08:04.821
All people who have flabby
hands and irritating laughs...

08:04.870 --> 08:06.781
They had the wrong floor.

08:06.830 --> 08:09.788
Law firm on the 18th
is expanding.

08:09.830 --> 08:12.617
Oh, my God.
What do we do?

08:12.660 --> 08:14.139
I called the insurance.

08:14.180 --> 08:15.488
We're covered.

08:15.530 --> 08:16.872
I have Shannon Janderman

08:16.930 --> 08:18.488
coming over tomorrow
to impress her.

08:18.540 --> 08:19.962
Well, we'll use
the conference room

08:20.020 --> 08:22.147
on the 27th floor.

08:22.190 --> 08:23.794
LUCCA: Uh, the paralegals
are in there.

08:23.850 --> 08:26.148
Okay, we'll think
of something.

08:26.200 --> 08:28.543
Diane, we have
to get back to court.

08:41.470 --> 08:43.995
There's another possibility.

08:44.040 --> 08:45.257
What's that?

08:45.300 --> 08:48.030
We expand to the 29th floor.

08:48.090 --> 08:49.512
What?

08:49.570 --> 08:51.174
We want to expand
and hire more lawyers.

08:51.220 --> 08:52.528
The 29th floor is empty.

08:52.570 --> 08:54.879
That equity firm
went bankrupt.
Yes.

08:54.920 --> 08:57.002
But we should expand because

08:57.050 --> 08:59.006
we decide to expand, not because

08:59.060 --> 09:00.834
someone accidentally
destroyed our conference room.

09:00.880 --> 09:02.359
Why not?

09:02.410 --> 09:04.401
[elevator bell dings]

09:06.370 --> 09:10.272
Matan Brody, Assistant State's
Attorney in Cook County.

09:10.330 --> 09:12.628
You were the lead prosecutor
in the Richard Locke case?

09:12.680 --> 09:14.238
With Cary Agos,
that's correct.

09:14.290 --> 09:15.803
CONNOR: Would you say Peter
Florrick micromanaged this case?

09:15.850 --> 09:18.728
I would.
And in what way
did he do that?

09:18.770 --> 09:20.761
Well, for one,
he came to the crime scene.

09:20.820 --> 09:22.981
CONNOR: He did?
On the night of the murder?

09:23.040 --> 09:24.905
Yes.

09:24.950 --> 09:26.554
CONNOR:
Is that unusual?

09:26.600 --> 09:27.942
MATAN: I've worked
with four SA's in 11 years.

09:28.000 --> 09:30.867
First time
I'd ever seen it.
Huh.

09:30.910 --> 09:34.175
So as the crime scene was being
processed, Peter was there?

09:34.220 --> 09:36.006
Yes. He asked a lot
of questions, he worried

09:36.050 --> 09:38.610
about their methods, their
experience, he had us review

09:38.660 --> 09:40.480
911 calls earlier in the week.

09:40.530 --> 09:42.316
And did this behavior continue?

09:42.360 --> 09:44.180
Yes, through prep,
right up until trial.

09:44.230 --> 09:45.618
Even the charging decision.

09:45.670 --> 09:47.399
We could've gone
for first degree murder,

09:47.450 --> 09:49.054
but he barely let us go
for second.

09:49.110 --> 09:52.716
CONNOR:
Thank you, Mr. Brody.

09:52.760 --> 09:54.409
DIANE:
The murder of

09:54.460 --> 09:56.803
Ms. Tanniston happened
just two weeks

09:56.850 --> 09:59.159
after Governor Elorrick
assumed office.

09:59.200 --> 10:00.679
Is that correct?Yes, I believe so.

10:00.730 --> 10:02.800
And this was Governor Florrick's
second stint

10:02.860 --> 10:04.589
as state's attorney

10:04.640 --> 10:06.596
after the corruption charges
against him

10:06.640 --> 10:08.198
had been thrown out?Yes.

10:08.250 --> 10:10.468
So, showing up
at a crime scene,

10:10.520 --> 10:12.954
making sure evidence
is collected properly--

10:13.000 --> 10:16.219
couldn't that be the action of
a re-elected state's attorney

10:16.260 --> 10:18.820
wanting to ensure
the-the highest standards?

10:18.870 --> 10:21.691
It could be, but it wasn't here.

10:23.230 --> 10:25.130
I see.

10:25.180 --> 10:27.660
How many gun felony charges
were thrown out

10:27.710 --> 10:30.668
under the previous
state's attorney, Glenn Childs?

10:30.710 --> 10:32.666
I don't know.

10:32.710 --> 10:34.268
625.

10:34.320 --> 10:36.584
That's over 12%.

10:36.630 --> 10:39.064
Do you know how many were
thrown out under Peter Florrick?

10:39.110 --> 10:41.192
Mr. Florrick was in office
for fewer yea rs.

10:41.240 --> 10:44.198
Well, I'm glad you're making
your bias evident.

10:44.250 --> 10:46.115
29 cases were
thrown out, Sir.

10:46.160 --> 10:47.718
That's fewer
than two percent.

10:47.770 --> 10:49.943
So it seems
that Peter Florrick's

10:49.990 --> 10:51.639
micromanagement was needed.

10:51.690 --> 10:52.850
It wasn't needed.
CONNOR:
Objection. Argumentative.

10:52.910 --> 10:54.514
Our department had double
the prosecutions

10:54.560 --> 10:56.608
before Peter Florrick.Of course you had double
the prosecutions

10:56.650 --> 10:58.208
because you didn't care
about the rule of law.Your Honor, I'm objecting here.

10:58.260 --> 10:59.989
This is not a debate.MATAN: Oh, that is such
defense attorney crap.

11:00.050 --> 11:01.039
[phone buzzing]

11:01.090 --> 11:03.046
[arguing over each other]

11:05.440 --> 11:06.566
[door opens]

11:06.620 --> 11:08.394
[door closes]Alicia.

11:08.450 --> 11:09.963
You're looking good.

11:10.010 --> 11:11.705
Thank you, so are you.

11:11.750 --> 11:12.830
You staying out of trouble?

11:12.880 --> 11:15.019
Trying.

11:15.060 --> 11:18.587
You seem to be drawing
a lot of interest.

11:18.630 --> 11:21.542
It happens when
your husband's on trial.

11:21.590 --> 11:25.026
So, is Cary
testifying against Peter?

11:25.070 --> 11:26.321
Let me ask you a question,

11:26.380 --> 11:28.245
is Peter
scapegoating Cary?
No.

11:28.290 --> 11:30.417
Then no.

11:30.470 --> 11:31.596
So we're linked?

11:31.640 --> 11:32.857
Well, you don't go after Cary,

11:32.900 --> 11:34.424
I have no reason
to go after Peter.

11:34.470 --> 11:36.597
Good.

11:36.650 --> 11:37.594
Then that's that.

11:37.650 --> 11:40.039
Not really.

11:40.090 --> 11:41.216
You have a problem.

11:44.440 --> 11:45.429
Peter is guilty.

11:48.220 --> 11:50.006
I have to get back to court,
Mr. Canning.

11:50.050 --> 11:51.005
Thank you.

11:51.050 --> 11:53.223
The AUSA has proof.

11:53.270 --> 11:55.534
They have a witness
who's not on the list.

11:55.580 --> 11:57.059
How do you know that?

11:57.100 --> 11:58.704
Because she approached us.
She wanted to know

11:58.760 --> 12:00.751
what Cary was gonna say.She? Who's she?

12:00.800 --> 12:02.051
Geneva Pine.

12:02.110 --> 12:04.670
If she testifies,
Peter goes to prison.

12:07.630 --> 12:09.507
What can she say?

12:09.550 --> 12:12.280
Everything.

